name: A5 Field binder
description:
An administrative case which protects your documnets and maps against water and dirt.

This administrative case is the result of 10 years of development and different generations of the cases.
The administrative case has one big pocket for reserve forms etc. On the outside of the case you will find a window pocket for maps, on the other side you have pocket for pens, a rubber and on the short side you have a pocket for a short ruler.
The inside has a removable mechanism for A5 papers. It has two window pockets for yellow stickers etc.
Loops of elastic cords are attached on the outside to secure pens and the compass.
A protective pocket on the top of the case can hold a light stick so you can read your documents without giving away your position.
A zips goes around the case and as backup it has two elastic bands which can be used instead of the zip.
The case has two elastic cords which you can tie your pens in.

Fits in:
A5 paper and block, pens, rubber, small ruler, maps, light stick and memo cards.

Fits on:
In your hand or inside the backpack

name: Squeeze ballistic front and back 1.3 S2
dimensions: Categories	Ballistic protection, Multicam, Vests & Chest rigs
description:
The Squeeze ballistic protection and equipment carrying system allows you to adapt the protection and the carrying capacity to meet your needs while taking weight, heat stress and other challenges into account.

The parts can be combined in many different ways depending on the threat, the mission and the environment.

The Squeeze can be carried in a system with the ballistic yoke, small ballistic sleeve set and ballistic groin protection set to make a really good protective set.

The vests in combination with the side panel pouches (84-00984) will fit 90% of the users.
The Squeeze sits very comfortable and tight on your body.
It is easy to adjust in height and width, even when worn.
The closure system with buckle or Velcro slosure is included.
Removable padded shoulder covers with cable channel and elastic loops for antennas.
Your radio ear piece can be placed under a flap in the shoulder cover when not in use.
Foam ridges on the inside for increased ventilation, comfort and lower trauma. Compartments for ballistic panels and ceramic plates on the front and back.
The bottom of the plate carrier is where the ballistic panels and plates are inserted or removed. This is also were you attach the groin protection when needed.
MOLLE webbing on the front and back.
One attachment point on each shoulder for a repair buckle to attach a backpack.
Two attachment points under the MOLLE webbings on the chest for repair buckles to attach the chest panel.
An elastic cord is placed around the edge of the front to hold hydration tubes or cables.
Velcro patches on the front and back for name and unit patches.

The product includes the following components:

Front carrier.
Back carrier.
Left and right shoulder cover.
Buckle closure
Velcro closure
Front plackard.

Note: The side panels, belt, yoke and groin protection are NOT included.

name: Comfort belt-13
description:
A padded belt with 2×25 MOLLE bands and one 10 mm webbing sewn on the outside for a comfortable carrying of any type of pouch or holster.
The MOLLE bands are sewn on 8 cm wide panels with slots between the panels. The inner belt can be placed on the outside of one or more panels so a pistol holster can be worn.
An inside 25 mm band is sewn under the panels, use it to attach a leg panel if you need to. It prevents the band from the leg panel from blocking other pouches on the belt itself.
In the top of the belt, loops are sewn so you can attach a harness or similar.
Ballistic panels can be inserted inside the belt.
Remove the waist band and use the riggers belt to combine the features of both belts.
A three point security buckle, prevents unwanted opening. The adjuster makes it easy to adjust the size of the equipment belt when you change from heavy winter clothing to lighter clothing.
The security band is used as usual on top of the adjuster. This adjuster is very neat when you are changing your clothing during the day. In the morning, it is cold and you wear more clothing. When it gets warmer and you remove some clothing, you need to tighten the belt, and then you use the belt adjuster.

XSmall: 65-95 cm
Small: 75-105 cm
Medium: 85-115 cm
Large: 95 -125 cm
XLarge: 105-135 cm
XXLarge: 115-145 cm
